events.name: QualityCheckInitiated
events.description: Represents the start of the quality check process for a batch of food imports.

events.name: QualityCheckPassed
events.description: Indicates that a batch has successfully passed the quality check.

events.name: QualityCheckFailed
events.description: Indicates that a batch has failed the quality check and must be rejected.

events.name: QualityReportGenerated
events.description: Represents the creation of a report detailing the results of the quality check.

events.name: QualityControlEscalation
events.description: Represents an issue during quality control that needs further attention from higher authority.

commands.name: InitiateQualityCheck
commands.description: Represents the start of the quality check process for a batch of food imports.

commands.name: ApproveBatch
commands.description: Indicates that a batch has successfully passed the quality check.

commands.name: RejectBatch
commands.description: Indicates that a batch has failed the quality check and must be rejected.

commands.name: GenerateQualityReport
commands.description: Represents the creation of a report detailing the results of the quality check.

commands.name: EscalateQualityIssue
commands.description: Represents an issue during quality control that needs further attention from higher authority.

integrationPoints.name: Inventory
integrationPoints.description: Integration with Inventory context to update stock levels based on quality check results.

integrationPoints.name: OrderManagement
integrationPoints.description: Integration with Order Management context to flag batches that are rejections.

integrationPoints.name: Reporting
integrationPoints.description: Integration with Reporting context to deliver quality check reports.
